  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (200b3f4 2023-05-05T00:04:08.284562894Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge create\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI am using below command:\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge create ./src/SimpleERC.sol:SimpleERC --rpc-url 'https://eth-goerli.g.alchemy.com/v2/'${ALCHEMY_ETH_GOERLI} --private-key ${PRIVATE_KEY} --force --constructor-args \"SimpleERC\" \"SERC\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nwith the simplest possible contract for ERC20 token like below:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity 0.8.18;\r\n\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract SimpleERC is ERC20 {\r\n    constructor() ERC20(\"SimpleERC\", \"SERC\") {\r\n        _mint(msg.sender, 100 * 10 ** decimals());\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo I believe this is not related to small amount of ETH on wallet. What it could be?",
